                                    <div class="row  mt-4 mb-0 mb-md-4">
                        <div class="col-12 col-md-6">
                            <aside class="author-name">
                                    
    
                                    
            By <a href="https://www.dukechronicle.com/staff/ben-cohen">Ben Cohen</a>
                                    
                                <div class="mt-1">
                                    <span class="can-localize">January 19, 2010 | 5:00am EST</span>
                                </div>
                            </aside>
                        </div>
                        <div class="col-12 col-md-6 text-left text-md-right d-print-none">
                            <ul class="social-links list-unsyled list-inline mt-4 mt-md-0">
                                <li class="list-inline-item"><a href="http://www.facebook.com/sharer.php?u=https://www.dukechronicle.com/article/2010/01/cutcliffes-message-hits-close-home" target="_blank" class="sends-events" data-ga-category="Share" data-ga-action="click" data-ga-label="facebook" data-ga-value="CURL"><i class="fab fa-facebook"></i></a></li>
                                <li class="list-inline-item"><a href="http://twitter.com/intent/tweet?url=https://www.dukechronicle.com/article/2010/01/cutcliffes-message-hits-close-home&amp;text=Cutcliffe&#039;s message hits close to home" target="_blank" class="sends-events" data-ga-category="Share" data-ga-action="click" data-ga-label="twitter" data-ga-value="CURL"><i class="fab fa-twitter"></i></a></li>
                                                                <li class="list-inline-item"><a href="mailto:?subject=Cutcliffe%27s%20message%20hits%20close%20to%20home%20|%20The%20Chronicle&amp;message=Check%20out%20this%20article%20from%20The%20Chronicle%3A%20https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dukechronicle.com%2Farticle%2F2010%2F01%2Fcutcliffes-message-hits-close-home" class="sends-events" data-ga-category="Share" data-ga-action="click" data-ga-label="email" data-ga-value="CURL"><i class="fa fa-envelope"></i></a></li>
                                <li class="list-inline-item"><a href="#" onclick="window.print()" class="sends-events" data-ga-category="Share" data-ga-action="click" data-ga-label="facebook" data-ga-value="CURL"><i class="fas fa-print"></i></a></li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                
                <div class="article-content w-100 mb-4">
                                            <p>Before walking into the Laurinburg Chamber of Commerce's annual membership meeting Tuesday night, David Cutcliffe left his phone in his truck. The next time Duke's head coach picked it up, he had about 80 text messages and 20 missed calls, and he was about to learn, in his words, &quot;how many e-mails and texts a BlackBerry can take at one time.&quot; Lane Kiffin had just announced he was leaving Knoxville for the glitz of Los Angeles, of course, but Cutcliffe didn't know that. &quot;I said, 'Holy smokes, World War III started, and everybody forgot to tell Scotland County,'&quot; <a href="http://www.sportingnews.com/college-football/article/2010-01-15/cutcliffe-might-be-one-last-big-decisions-i-make">he told The Sporting News.</a>&nbsp;</p>
<div style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px;">These past few weeks<span style="font-family: sans-serif;">&mdash;</span>and more locally, last two days<span style="font-family: sans-serif;">&mdash;</span>have been about as close to a turf war as a college football coaching search can get. By Friday morning, about 60 hours after the blitz began, Duke Football, improbably and somewhat shockingly, escaped battle as a winner.&nbsp;</div>

                        <div class="inline-ad float-none float-md-left my-4 mr-0 mr-md-4 text-center d-print-none">
                            <!-- START gryphon/ads/rectangle-inline.tpl -->
            <div id="azk18664"></div>
    <!-- END gryphon/ads/rectangle-inline.tpl -->
                        </div>

                        <div style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px;">&nbsp;</div>
<div style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px;">That's not something you hear every day.</div>
<div style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px;">&nbsp;</div>
<div style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px;">We're also not used to seeing highlights of Duke's football coach on loop on national television. ESPN's star pundits aren't accustomed to publicly and constantly touting Duke's football coach. And Duke's football coach doesn't regularly turn down overtures from other schools, let alone Tennessee&mdash;a real football school, one with a fan base whose passion rivals, if not exceeds, those who follow the goings-on in Cameron Indoor Stadium. (Trust me on the Volunteer faithful's zeal. I've read far too many Tennessee message boards in the last 72 hours. My browser aches from refreshing.)</div>
<div style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px;">&nbsp;</div>
<div style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px;">It's true that when <a href="http://dukechronicle.com/article/cutcliffe-turns-down-tennessee-will-stay-duke">Cutcliffe released his statement announcing his return</a> at a time most undergraduates were still sleeping on Friday, nothing had changed. At 9:09 a.m. Wednesday, Cutcliffe was Duke's head coach. He was on Thursday at 9:09 a.m., and on Friday, he most certainly was. The assistants were the same. The workout schedule was the same. The players were the same.&nbsp;</div>

                        <div class="inline-ad float-none float-md-left my-4 mr-0 mr-md-4 text-center d-print-none">
                            <!-- START gryphon/ads/rectangle-article-5.tpl -->
        <div id="azk5125"></div>
<!-- END gryphon/ads/rectangle-article-5.tpl -->
                        </div>

                                                                            <div style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px;">&nbsp;</div>
<div style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px;">As much as nothing had changed since Tuesday night, though&mdash;well, a lot had.</div>
<div style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px;">&nbsp;</div>
<div style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px;">It was impossible to watch ESPN for an hour without hearing Cutcliffe's name, without being inundated by analysts extolling Cutcliffe's credentials and, on Friday, without learning that a certain football coach had turned down Tennessee to stay at Duke. Quick, send some thank-you notes to Lane Kiffin. He's given Duke Football about as much publicity&mdash;and the right kind, too&mdash;as the program's had in longer than anyone living on campus can remember.</div>
                            

<div class="mc-signup my-4 p-4 text-center " id="mc-container" data-mc="58dfdea1a4">
    <h3>Get Overtime, all Duke athletics</h3>
    <p>Signup for our editorially curated, weekly newsletter. Cancel at any time.</p>
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col col-md-8 offset-md-2">
            <form action="//dukechronicle.us4.list-manage.com/subscribe/post?u=c49dc69f492af7f2727860d0b&amp;id=58dfdea1a4" method="post">
